Column Comment.0: RESERVES ENTITY IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for a reserves entity. A reservesentity may be comprised of a single business object (such as a well) or a group ofbusiness objects (such as all the completions producing from a pool).
Column Comment.1: RESERVE CLASS IDENTIFIER: The reserve classed for identifying the confidencelevel and producing status of the reserve volumes.
Column Comment.2: RESERVES ENTITY ECONOMICS RUN IDENTIFIER: a unique identifer for aneconomics run
Column Comment.3: PRODUCT_TYPE: The product identified as a component for this table.
Column Comment.4: ECONOMIC VOLUME SUMMARY OBSERVATION NUMBER: A unique numberidentifying individual volumes related to the economic summary.
Column Comment.5: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.6: EFFECTIVE DATE: date on which the data in this row came into effect.
Column Comment.7: EXPIRY DATE: Date on which the data in this row of data was no longer in effect.
Column Comment.8: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.9: REMAINING BALANCE: The volume of economic reserves remaining as of theremaining balance date.
Column Comment.10: REMAINING BALANCE DATE: The date beyond which the remaining reserves willbe produced.
Column Comment.11: REMAINING BALANCE DATE DESCRIPTION: Use this column to define the level ofprecision in the DATE format colums, such as YYYY, or YYYQQ, or YYYYMM orYYYYMMDD
Column Comment.12: ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE: Original unit of measure for a value.
Column Comment.13: UNITS OF MEASURE: Units of measure for a value.
Column Comment.14: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.15: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.16: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.17: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.18: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.19: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.20: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.21: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.22: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
